    <head>
        <style>
            .mb-auto {
                height: 100%;
            }

            h1 {
                text-align: center;
                font-size: 22px !important;
                display: block;
                margin-bottom: 16px;
            }

            h2 {
                font-size: 22px !important;
            }

            .section-title {
                font-weight: bold;
                font-size:0.97em
                margin-top: 10px;
            }

            .content {
                margin-left: 20px;
               font-size:0.87em
            }

            .title {
                font-size: 20px;
            }

            table {
               font-size:0.87em
                margin-left: 20px;
                border: 1px solid black !important;
                border-collapse: collapse !important;
                width: 85%;
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
            }

            th,
            td {
                border: 1px solid black !important;
                padding: 5px;
                width: 50%;
            }

            body {
                font-size: 16px;
                background: white;
            }

            .accept-section {
                border-top: 1px solid #4A4A4A;
                position: sticky;
                bottom: -1px;
                left: 0;
                width: 100%;
                background-color: white; /* Adjust to match your design */
                text-align: center;
                z-index: 1000; /* Ensure it's above other elements */
            }
            .btn-primary{
                padding: 0.5rem 0.875rem;
                font-size: 0.875rem;
                line-height: 1.5;
                border-radius: 1.5rem;
                margin-top: 0.5rem;
                background-image: unset;
                color: white;
            }

            @media(max-width: 788px){
                h1{
                    font-size: 28px !important;
                }
                h2{
                    font-size: 19px !important;
                }
                p{
                    font-size: 12px !important;
                }
                .title{
                    font-size: 15px;
                }
                h3{
                    font-size: 14px;
                }
                table{
                    font-size: 14px;
                }
            }
            @media(max-width: 450px){
                h1{
                    font-size: 20px !important;
                }
                h2{
                    font-size: 17px !important;
                }
                p{
                    font-size: 10px !important;
                }
                .title{
                    font-size: 14px;
                }
                h3{
                    font-size: 13px;
                }
                table{
                    font-size: 8px;
                }
            }
        </style>

    </head>

    <apex:form >
        <apex:actionFunction name="updateDetails" action="{!updatePSASignFields}" oncomplete="sendMessageToParent();"/>
    </apex:form>

    <apex:outputPanel rendered="{!OR(showPSA,CompanyName='test identity 1')}">

        <div class="d-flex flex-column h-100">
            <div class="mb-auto" id="content">
                <h1>EMPLOYEE SPONSORSHIP AGREEMENT</h1>
                <p class="title">This Employee Sponsorship Agreement (the "<b>ESA</b>") is made on <strong>
                        <apex:outputText value=" {0,date, MMM d, yyyy}">
                            <apex:param value="{!AgreementDate}" />
                        </apex:outputText>
                    </strong></p>

                <h2>Between</h2>
                <p>1. <strong>Dubai Development Authority</strong>, a body corporate established under Law No. 1 of 2000,
                    with
                    address at Second Floor Building No.2 Dubai Studio City, P.O. Box 478844, Dubai, United Arab Emirates
                    ("<b>DDA</b>"),</p>
                <p>and</p>
                <p>2. <strong>{!companyName}</strong>, a company registered in the Dubai Development Authority Zones under
                    Licence number <strong>{!LicenseNumber}</strong> (the "<b>Employer</b>").</p>
                <p>(DDA and the Employer are also referred to separately as a "<b>Party</b>" and jointly as the
                    "<b>Parties</b>").</p>
                <h2>WHEREAS</h2>
                <p class="content">A. The Employer is a duly licensed business in the Zone.</p>
                <p class="content">B. The Employer wishes to engage Employee(s) for its business in the Zone.</p>
                <p class="content">C. DDA is authorized to sponsor employee(s) to be engaged to work for an Employer in the
                    Zone.</p>

                <h2>IT IS AGREED AS FOLLOWS</h2>
                <br /><br />
                <h3 class="section-title">1. DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION</h3>
                <p>1.1 The following defined terms have the meaning given below unless the context implies otherwise: </p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Authority</b>" means the Dubai Development Authority or herein also referred to as
                    DDA.
                </p>
                <p class="content">"<b>DIFC Courts</b>" the courts of the Dubai International Financial Centre in the
                    Emirate of
                    Dubai.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Dubai Courts</b>"the courts of the Emirate of Dubai established pursuant to Law
                    Courts
                    Formation No. (3) of 1992 in the Emirate of Dubai and its amendments.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Employee(s)</b>" means any eligible individual authorized by the Authority to work
                    for a
                    Licensee including without limitation Sponsored Employees and non-sponsored employees, receiving any
                    kind of
                    remuneration whether such payments are made in cash or in kind, for work he performs in the service of a
                    Licensee and under the Licensee's management and control.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Employer</b>"any entity or company holding a valid licence issued under the Licensing
                    Regulations and the Private Companies Regulations of the Authority, and all its amendments. For the
                    purposes
                    of this ESA, Licensee shall be referred to alternatively as Employer. </p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Employee Allocation</b>" means the maximum number of employees which an Employer is
                    permitted to employ in the Zone based on the Employer's permitted activities and area leased or owned in
                    the
                    Zone, as prescribed by DDA from time to time.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Employment Contract</b>" means the employment contract and the key employment terms
                    duly
                    executed and submitted by the Licensee to the Authority and as amended accordingly .</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Employee Regulations</b>" means the Dubai Technology and Media Free Zone Employment
                    Regulations of 2004 and its amendments.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>ESA</b>" means this employee sponsorship agreement signed between DDA and the
                    Employer
                    for the Sponsorship of an employee.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Fees</b>" means the fees charged by DDA in consideration for the provision of the
                    Sponsorship, such Fees being subject to amendment by DDA at its sole discretion on notice to the
                    Employer.
                </p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Guarantee</b>" means an unconditional and absolute guarantee issued by a Licensee in
                    favour of the Authority in a form implemented by the Authority from time to time.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Immigration Law</b>" means the Immigration Law being Federal Law No. 6 of 1973 (as
                    may be
                    amended from time to time).</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Labour Law</b>" means the Federal Decree-Law No. 33 of 2021 on the Regulation of
                    Employment Regulations, Standard General Rules of Work in the UAE, implementing regulations and its
                    amendments.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Licence</b>" means a current and valid licence issued by DDA allowing the Employer to
                    legally undertake activities in the Zone.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Minimum Conditions</b>" means the minimum employment conditions required by the
                    Labour
                    Law including without limitation in relation to remuneration, working hours, working conditions,
                    holidays,
                    leaves, salary, or hourly rate, notice provisions and end of service benefit as prescribed under the DDA
                    Employment regulations.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Penal Code</b>" means the Penal Code of the UAE being Federal Law No 3 of 1987 as
                    amended.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Sponsored Employee</b>" means an individual sponsored by the Authority pursuant to
                    the
                    employee sponsorship agreement and in accordance with the provisions of the Licensing Regulations, this
                    Policy, and any amendments thereof.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Sponsorship</b>"means the sponsorship of employees by DDA in accordance with the
                    Immigration Law and the Employment Regulations for the purposes of residence and employment in the Zone.
                </p>
                <p class="content">"<b>UAE</b>" means the United Arab Emirates.</p>
                <p class="content">"<b>Zone</b>" means the areas under the jurisdiction of the Authority established in the
                    Emirate of Dubai pursuant to Law No. 1 of 2000 and its amendments. </p>

                <p>1.2 Unless the context otherwise requires, in this ESA: </p>
                <p class="content">(a)&nbsp;&nbsp;a reference to any statute or statutory provisions shall include any
                    statute or statutory
                    provision which amends or replaces or has amended or replaced it and shall include any subordinate
                    legislation made under the relevant statute.</p>
                <p class="content">(b)&nbsp;&nbsp;words denoting the singular number shall include the plural and vice versa
                    and reference to
                    the masculine gender includes a reference to the feminine gender and neuter and vice versa.</p>
                <p class="content">(c)&nbsp;&nbsp;references to sections, clauses and sub-clauses are to be construed as
                    references to the
                    sections, clauses, and sub-clauses of this ESA.</p>
                <p class="content">(d)&nbsp;&nbsp;costs, charges, expenses, or remuneration shall be deemed to include, in
                    addition, references
                    to any value added tax or similar tax charged or chargeable in respect thereof.</p>
                <p class="content">(e)&nbsp;&nbsp;references to "writing" includes telex, facsimile and other forms of
                    written material
                    transmitted electronically or digitally.</p>
                <p class="content">(f)&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of any inconsistency in this ESA or between this ESA and any
                    other agreement
                    (signed by the Employer or otherwise), the Authority (herein represented by the Deputy Director General
                    –
                    Business Affairs) will determine the correct interpretation and the Employer shall be so bound.</p>
                <p class="content">(g)&nbsp;&nbsp; Any word(s) used in this ESA that are not defined in the Definitions
                    shall have the meaning
                    as contemplated under the DDA Visa Policy and the respective DDA Decision or Regulation. </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">2. SPONSORSHIP CONDITIONS</h3>
                <p class="content">2.1 The Employer agrees, that DDA shall sponsor the employee in accordance to the terms
                    and
                    conditions of this ESA Any schedule, annexures, or amendment to this Agreement forms an integral part
                    of
                    this ESA.</p>
                <p class="content">2.2 The Employer shall maintain at all times a valid licence to carry on business in the
                    Zone.</p>
                <p class="content">2.3 Every sponsorship is strictly subject to the employee being suitable for employment
                    and
                    residence in the UAE in terms of Immigration Law and Labour Law. The Employer warrants that it has
                    verified
                    the credentials of each employee as represented in the application for the employee's residence and work
                    permit.</p>
                <p class="content">2.4 DDA shall prescribe, at its sole discretion, the number of employees that an Employer
                    can
                    employ in accordance with the policy implemented by DDA from time to time.</p>
                <p class="content">2.5 An employee is only allowed to work in the Zone. However, there may be occasions when
                    an
                    Employer requires an employee to work temporarily outside the Zone or within the Zone (on a temporary or
                    secondment basis), in each case, DDA's prior written approval is required.</p>
                <p class="content">2.6 The Authority may at its sole discretion, terminate or cancel the sponsorship of any
                    Sponsored Employee at any time and for any reason, or no reason at all, with written notice to the
                    Employer.
                    The Employer shall pay all the Sponsored Employee's entitlements as per the Employment Contract and the
                    Labour Law accrued till the date of cancellation of the sponsorship of the Sponsored Employee.</p>

                <h3 class="section-title">3. EMPLOYER OBLIGATIONS</h3>
                <p class="content">3.1 The Employer shall be liable to pay any or all Fees in connection with the
                    Sponsorship
                    (including without limitation processing the entry permit, air fare, processing the residence permit and
                    renewals thereof, including the cost of a medical fitness certificate and the fees for the emirates
                    identification card). The Employer shall pay such Fees immediately and without any withholding or delay
                    on
                    account of any claim, counterclaim, set-off or otherwise.</p>
                <p class="content">3.2 The Employer shall provide DDA with a certificate of insurance from an insurer
                    licensed
                    and operating in the UAE confirming that insurance has been affected by the Employer for:</p>
                <p class="content">3.2.1 workmen's compensation for a reasonable amount or for such minimum amount as DDA
                    may
                    prescribe from time to time; and</p>
                <p class="content">3.2.2 cover against third party claims that may arise through the act of the Sponsored
                    Employee or otherwise through the performance of the Sponsorship Agreement.</p>
                <p class="content">Such insurance to be reasonably satisfactory to DDA.</p>
                <p class="content">3.3 The Employer shall act as principal in regard to the Sponsored Employee's
                    remuneration
                    and any other payments and emoluments due to the Sponsored Employee in accordance with the terms of the
                    Sponsored Employee's Employment Contract and the key employment terms, the UAE Labour Law, and the
                    Employee
                    Sponsorship ESA. DDA shall not be responsible in any way whatsoever for the remuneration or any other
                    payments or emoluments of a Sponsored Employee including without limitation to any related cost for the
                    purpose of sponsorship.</p>
                <p class="content">3.4 Without limiting the provision of clause 3.2 above, the Employer shall ensure at all
                    times, to subscribe the Sponsored Employees to appropriate health insurance coverage and the Employer
                    shall
                    at all times comply with the applicable law with respect to medical or health coverage requirements.
                </p>
                <p class="content">3.5 The Employer is prohibited from charging the costs or Fees to the Sponsored Employee,
                    or
                    from recouping such costs by making deductions from the Sponsored Employee's salary, remuneration or any
                    benefits unless the Labour Law indicates otherwise.</p>
                <p class="content">3.6 The Employer shall at all times comply with all applicable UAE and DDA laws and
                    regulations and the requirements of any relevant authority in the conduct of its business and shall take
                    the
                    necessary actions to ensure that the Sponsored Employee and all its employees are aware of his rights
                    and
                    obligations under this ESA and all applicable laws and regulations in the performance of his work.</p>
                <p class="content">3.7 An Employer shall ensure to register or enroll with DDA's wage protection system or
                    similar scheme as may be implemented by DDA and ensure that employee's salaries and emoluments or dues
                    have
                    been paid on time. </p>
                <p class="content">3.8 The Employer must notify DDA of any disciplinary action taken against a Sponsored
                    Employee within 10 days of the action being taken. The information includes the name and identification
                    number of the Sponsored Employee, date of the alleged offence committed by the Sponsored Employee,
                    nature of
                    the alleged offence committed by the Sponsored Employee, disciplinary action taken by the Employer. </p>
                <p class="content">3.9 The Employer shall be responsible for payment of medical treatment, including
                    hospitalization costs required by a non-sponsored or Sponsored Employee being exposed to one of the
                    occupational diseases specified under the Labour Law or any other injuries arising therefrom, due to or
                    occurring in the course of work. Any injury should be considered a work injury if it is proven that the
                    accident happened to the worker during the period of his commute to and from work, without interruption
                    or
                    deviation from the normal route. </p>
                <p class="content">3.10 Unless the Sponsored Employee obtains a new residence and work permit within thirty
                    (30)
                    days from the date of termination of his Employment Contract, the Employer shall apply immediately to
                    DDA
                    for the cancellation of the residence and work permit and provide the Sponsored Employee with an air
                    ticket
                    subject to the conditions prescribed under the Labour Law.</p>
                <p class="content">3.11 In addition to the agreed obligations of the Employer under this ESA, the Employer
                    shall
                    comply with all its obligations as expressed under the Labour Law. </p>


                <h3 class="section-title">4. EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT</h3>
                <p class="content">4.1 The Employer shall execute the Employment Contract for each employee it engages.</p>
                <p class="content">4.2 The Employer and a Sponsored Employee may negotiate the terms and conditions of
                    employment, provided the agreement is not contrary to this ESA and is in accordance with the Employment
                    Regulations and the Labour Law.</p>
                <p class="content">4.3 A signed copy of the Employment Contract will be deposited by the Employer to DDA.
                </p>
                <p class="content">4.4 The Employer must maintain the employee's files and records as per the conditions,
                    rules
                    and procedures issued by the Authority, provided that the period of keeping the employee's file shall
                    not be
                    less than two years after the date of the employee's end of service. The Employer shall supply to DDA
                    all
                    relevant details concerning the employee as requested by DDA from time to time including the signed
                    Employment Contract.</p>
                <p class="content">4.5 To resolve any other dispute arising out of or in connection with the Employment
                    Contract
                    (including a dispute regarding the existence, validity or termination of the Employment Contract and the
                    consequences of its nullity), the Employer and the employee submits to the jurisdiction of the Dubai
                    Courts
                    or, if the Employer and employee have so agreed in the Employment Contract, the DIFC Courts.</p>

                <h3 class="section-title">5. GUARANTEE</h3>
                <p class="content">5.1 The Employer shall provide a Guarantee, or any other security approved by DDA in
                    respect
                    of each Sponsored Employee. </p>
                <p class="content">5.2 The Employer shall provide DDA with a cash deposit or a Guarantee in the amount of
                    AED
                    2500 per Sponsored Employee and shall be adjusted based on the applicable Employee Allocation and as
                    prescribed under the DDA Visa Policy . The aforementioned cash deposit or the Guarantee shall be
                    returned to
                    the Employer upon the cancellation of the Employer's Licence and the cancellation of all Sponsorships.
                </p>
                <p class="content">5.3 Where Employer employs more than fifty (50) Employees, the Guarantee shall not exceed
                    the
                    amount of United Arab Emirates Dirhams One Hundred and Twenty-Five Thousand (AED 125,000.00). </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">6. NO LIABILITY ON DDA</h3>
                <p class="content">6.1 DDA shall not be liable under any circumstance to the Employer for any act, default,
                    or
                    omission on the part of an employee including without limitation any breach by any of the employee of
                    any
                    restraint of trade or non-competition covenant that may be contained in the Employment Contract
                    following
                    completion or termination of the employment of any of the employee. </p>
                <p class="content">6.2 For the purposes of the Sponsorship, DDA shall act as the pure agent of the Employer
                    and
                    the Employment Contract shall constitute a primary obligation on the part of the Employer to the
                    Sponsored
                    Employee.</p>
                <p class="content">6.3 The Employer shall be solely responsible for the rights of his employees including
                    without limitation any and all amounts due to the employees whether under the Employment Contract or at
                    law,
                    and for all amounts due to the federal government or individual emirate authorities in relation to the
                    residence and employment in the UAE of the employees and no amount shall be payable by DDA whatsoever by
                    reason of DDA's Sponsorship of the employees and the Employer shall indemnify DDA for any and all
                    amounts,
                    costs or entitlements that may be claimed whether by the employees or by third parties in relation to
                    the
                    Sponsorship. </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">7. INDEMNITY</h3>
                <p class="content">The Employer shall indemnify and keep indemnified DDA against any and all actions,
                    claims,
                    liabilities, losses, damages, costs or expenses of any nature whatsoever (including legal fees incurred
                    in
                    connection herewith) in relation to any action by the Employer or the Sponsored Employee or by any third
                    party and against all losses or damage to any property (including property of DDA) which may arise in
                    consequence of the performance of the ESA.</p>

                <h3 class="section-title">8. TERMINATION OF AGREEMENT</h3>
                <p class="content">8.1 DDA may terminate this ESA immediately, in any of the following events:</p>
                <p class="content">8.1.1 DDA or other relevant authority does not renew or cancel the Employer's Licence or
                    the
                    non-compliance by the Employer with the applicable rules and regulations of DDA.</p>
                <p class="content">8.1.2 the termination or non-renewal of any lease agreement by the Employer in the Zone.
                </p>
                <p class="content">8.1.3 the breach of any terms, conditions, or obligations by the Employer under this ESA.
                </p>
                <p class="content">8.1.4 the breach of any terms, conditions, or obligations by the Employer under the
                    Employment Contract. </p>
                <p class="content">8.1.5 the Employer becomes bankrupt, enters into liquidation, whether compulsorily or
                    voluntarily, has a receiver appointed or takes any steps to wind itself up.</p>
                <p class="content">8.2 Subject to the approval of the Authority, the Employer may request the termination or
                    cancellation of the Sponsorship of the Sponsored Employee upon the occurrence of any one of the
                    circumstances enumerated under Article 42 of the Labour Law </p>
                <p class="content">8.3 DDA may terminate the Sponsorship of the Sponsored Employee immediately on the date
                    of
                    termination of his Employment Contract (this being the last day of work, including the contractual
                    notice
                    period) unless such Employment Contract is otherwise renewed by the Employer and the Sponsored Employee.
                </p>
                <p class="content">8.4 The expiry or termination of this ESA for any reason shall be without prejudice to
                    any
                    obligations which may have occurred upon the Parties prior to the date thereof. </p>
                <p class="content">8.5 This ESA may be cancelled at any time by DDA for any reason whatsoever by providing
                    the
                    Employer with fourteen (14) calendar days written notice. </p>
                <p class="content">8.6 A breach of the ESA by the Employer will be deemed a breach by DDA for the purpose of
                    Article 10.1.11 of the DCC Licensing Regulations 2003 as well as a breach of the Employment Regulations
                    and
                    may lead to a suspension or termination of the Employer's licence. </p>
                <p class="content">8.7 The Sponsored Employee may, in case of expiry of the Employment Contract or at any
                    time
                    during the term of the Employment Contract (subject to compliance with the provisions of the Employment
                    Contract) in accordance with the provisions hereof, move to work for another Licensee or Employer as per
                    the
                    conditions and procedures prescribed by the Authority. </p>
                <p class="content">The Employer may assign the Sponsored Employee to another company for purposes of
                    providing
                    its services to such company subject to the condition that the Employer shall be solely liable in this
                    case
                    for the rights of the Sponsored Employee who are undertaking this work, which accrue to them in
                    accordance
                    with the provisions of the Employment Contract and the Labour Law. </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">9. NOTICES</h3>
                <p class="content">Any notice or other communications to be given to either DDA or the Employer in respect
                    of
                    any matter for the ESA may be given by hand, registered post, electronically, digitally, or facsimile to
                    the
                    respective addresses of DDA and the Employer as set out in the ESA. In the case of notices to the
                    Employer,
                    DDA is entitled to rely on the last recorded details for the Employer as set out in the Employer's
                    Licence.
                </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">10. NO WAIVER</h3>
                <p class="content">Failure by DDA on any occasion to insist upon observance or performance by the Employer
                    of
                    any covenant or obligation herein shall not amount to a waiver of such breach or acceptance of such
                    variation by DDA. Furthermore, no waiver by DDA of any breach of any covenant, obligation or provisions
                    under these terms and conditions express or implied shall operate as waiver of another breach of the
                    same or
                    of any covenant, obligation or provision under these terms and conditions express or implied.</p>

                <h3 class="section-title">11. SEVERABILITY</h3>
                <p class="content">Each provision of this ESA (including each undertaking and part thereof) shall be
                    construed
                    separately and independently from each other provision and notwithstanding that such provision and/or
                    undertaking (or any part thereof) may prove to be illegal or unenforceable the remaining provisions and
                    undertakings of this ESA shall continue in full force and effect. </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">12. LANGUAGE</h3>
                <p class="content">These general terms and conditions have been drafted in the English Language. In the
                    event of
