                    shall
                    be construed as if such phrases, sentences, clauses, or paragraphs had not been inserted in the ESA.
                </p>

                <h3 class="section-title">15. GENERAL </h3>
                <p class="content">15.1 <b>Assignment.</b> The Employer shall not assign any of its obligations and duties
                    under
                    this ESA. DDA may assign or otherwise transfer the ESA to any Affiliate, associated entity or third
                    party.
                </p>
                <p class="content">15.2 <b>Electronic Execution.</b> The words “execution,” “signed,” “signature,” and words
                    of
                    similar import in this ESA shall be deemed to include electronic and digital signatures and the keeping
                    of
                    records in electronic form, each of which shall be of the same effect, validity, and enforceability as
                    manually executed signatures and paper-based recordkeeping systems, to the extent and as provided for
                    under
                    applicable law, including the Electronic Transactions Law (Law No. (1) of 2006 On Electronic Commerce
                    and
                    Transactions), the Federal Law No. 10 of 1992 concerning Law of Evidence in Civil and Commercial
                    Transactions (as amended by Federal Law No. 36 of 2006)) which clarifies that Electronic Signatures (as
                    defined under the Electronic Transactions Law) and the Ministerial Resolution (Minister of Economy
                    Resolution No. 1 of 2008 issuing the list of the Electronic Certification Services Providers), which
                    addresses regulation of Certification Service Providers (as defined under the Electronic Transactions
                    Law)
                    by the Telecommunications and Digital Government Regulatory Authority and the implementing policies
                    issued
                    by DDA in this regard.</p>
                <p class="content">15.3 <b>Variation and Amendments.</b> DDA may at its sole discretion vary at any time the
                    terms and conditions of this ESA, and the Employer agrees to execute the amendment or variation thereof.
                </p>

